SU(2) partial-character gamma diagnostic
Date: 2026-07-23

Strict build:
  g++ -O2 -std=c++20 \
    -Wall -Wextra -Wpedantic -Wconversion -Wshadow -Werror \
    ginibre_q3/character_ring_iter/search_su2_partial_character_cone.cpp \
    -o /tmp/search_su2_partial_character_cone

Gamma-mode obstruction:
  /tmp/search_su2_partial_character_cone 4 6 gamma
  GAMMA_FAIL factors=[-1,+1] gamma_index=1 coefficient=-1 tested=4

Exact interpretation:
  G_R=chi_2
  A_R(t)=1+t+t^2=(1+t)^2-t
  gamma(A_R)=(1,-1)

Original partial-character regression:
  /tmp/search_su2_partial_character_cone 3 5
  SU2_PARTIAL_CHARACTER_CONE PASS tested=1022 \
    maximum_label=3 maximum_factors=5

The obstruction refutes gamma positivity only.  It does not refute
palindromic unimodality or the partial-character conjecture.

Log-concavity obstruction:
  /tmp/search_su2_partial_character_cone 4 6 logconcave
  LOGCONCAVITY_FAIL factors=[+1,+4,+4] \
    coefficient_index=3 coefficient=-1 tested=5003

Exact interpretation:
  G_R=3 chi_1+2 chi_3+2 chi_5+2 chi_7+chi_9
  A_R coefficients=[1,3,5,7,10,10,7,5,3,1]
  7^2-5*10=-1

This polynomial remains nonnegative, palindromic, and unimodal.  The
obstruction rules out log-concavity as a route to the required
unimodality.
